      "sourceStatus": "CORRECTION_REQUIRED",
      "sourceText": "Heads Up, Folks! The Discs Are Flying Again",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0013",
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "This is an artist's conception of the flying disc that A. C. Urie saw sweeping through Snake river canyon six miles west of Blue Lakes ranch. It seemed to be powered by jets emitting a fiery glow on both sides, and could well be the inspiration for something new in women's hats, such as a \"flying saucer\" creation. (Drawing by Vic Goertzen, staff engraving)",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
