      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0016",
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "sourceStatus": "CORRECTION_REQUIRED",
      "sourceText": "At 1,000 Miles Per Hour; Two Others Are Seen",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0018",
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "Just as Magic Valley and the nation were starting to let go of lampposts after reeling under a welter of flying saucer reports, two more Twin Falls county men revived speculation on the mystery with vivid descriptions of discs they saw.",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0019",
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "From A. C. Urie, who operates the Auger Falls Trout farm six miles west of Blue Lakes ranch in Snake river canyon, came perhaps the most detailed account of one of the fast-flying objects the nation has yet produced.",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0020",
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "The flying saucer Urie saw was skimming along through Snake river canyon at a height of about 75 feet at 1 p. m. Wednesday. At 9:30 a. m. the same day, L. W. Hawkins, Twin Falls county commissioner and former county sheriff from Filer, also saw two circular objects soaring along at a great height near Salmon dam 40 miles southwest of Twin Falls.",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0021",
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "Here is Urie's eye-witness description of the flying discs seen by him and his son, Keith, 8, and Billy, 10:",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0022",
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "\"I obtained a close-up view of the flying saucer as it passed by the trout farm at 1 p. m. Aug. 13 going down Snake river canyon at a height of about 75 feet from the canyon floor. I would estimate the speed at about 1,000 miles per hour.\"",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0023",
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "Urie explained that the incident occurred while the two boys were coming across the river from the north side in a boat. He had become concerned about what was delaying them, and had walked down toward the river to see if they were all right.",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
    {
      "part": 4,
      "page": 41,
      "pageId": "page_0041",
      "lineId": "page_0041-l0024",
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "sourceStatus": "NEEDS_IMAGE_CHECK",
      "sourceText": "\"I had a side view at a distance of about 300 feet and almost on a level with the thing,\" Urie continued, \"Two of my boys, Keith and Billy, were below me and they also saw it at about a 45-degree angle. They both got a bottom and a side view, and we were all looking at it from the south side of the",
      "reason": "line_not_translation_ready",
      "translationUse": "excluded_from_public_translation_body"
    },
